RustPythonKotlinSwift <p>Add the <code>nostr</code> dependency in your <code>Cargo.toml</code> file:</p> <pre><code>[dependencies]
nostr = "0.25"
</code></pre> <p>Alternatively, you can add it directly from <code>git</code> source:</p> <pre><code>[dependencies]
nostr = { git = "https://github.com/rust-nostr/nostr", tag = "v0.25.0" }
</code></pre> <p>Note</p> <p>To use a specific commit, use <code>rev</code> instead of <code>tag</code>.</p> <p>Import the library in your code:</p> <pre><code>use nostr::prelude::*;
</code></pre> <p>The <code>nostr-protocol</code> package is available on the public PyPI:</p> <pre><code>pip install nostr-protocol </code></pre> <p>Import the library in your code:</p> <pre><code>from nostr_protocol import *
</code></pre> <p>To use the Kotlin language bindings for <code>nostr</code> in your Android project add the following to your gradle dependencies:</p> <pre><code>repositories {
mavenCentral()
}

dependencies { implementation("io.github.rust-nostr:nostr:&lt;version&gt;")
}
</code></pre> <p>Import the library in your code:</p> <pre><code>import nostr.*
</code></pre>

RustPythonKotlinSwift <pre><code>use nostr::prelude::*;

fn main() -&gt; Result&lt;()&gt; {
let keys = Keys::generate();

let public_key = keys.public_key();
let secret_key = keys.secret_key()?;

println!("Public key (hex): {}", public_key);
println!("Public key (bech32): {}", public_key.to_bech32()?);
println!("Secret key (hex): {}", keys.secret_key()?.display_secret());
println!("Secret key (bech32): {}", secret_key.to_bech32()?);
}
</code></pre> <pre><code>from nostr_protocol import Keys

keys = Keys.generate()
public_key = keys.public_key()
secret_key = keys.secret_key()
print("Keys:")
print(" Public keys:")
print(f"     hex:    {public_key.to_hex()}")
print(f"     bech32: {public_key.to_bech32()}")
print(" Secret keys:")
print(f"     hex:    {secret_key.to_hex()}")
print(f"     bech32: {secret_key.to_bech32()}")
